Parsons, who was driving, stopped at the Engen garage on Tara Road. Orson went into the shop and heard what sounded like fireworks. He did not think much of the noise. When he stepped out of the shop, he saw his wife lying bleeding on the ground. Their daughter was unharmed. Garrith Jamieson, Rescue Care paramedics spokesperson, said they found Parsons on the ground. She had sustained gunshot wounds to her upper body and was declared dead. Orson was too distraught to speak to the media at their Bluff home. Colonel Thembeka Mbhele, a police spokesperson, said the motive was unknown. Wentworth police are investigating. Daily News